The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | 13 test positive
                                                                                                                       7                                      13 test positive
            OUR CORRESPONDENT                      
	Chandigarh: Thirteen kabaddi players of the Indian team were tested positive during the trials for the 10-team World Cup Kabaddi Punjab (WCKP), to be held here from April 3-12.         
	The urine samples were collected during the trials held on March 20, state sports director Pargat Singh said.         
	Pargat said that the players have been provisionally suspended and will not be allowed to participate in the tournament. They have also asked to appear before the anti-doping tribunal, headed by Dr Manmohan Singh. Apart from hosts India, UK, US, Canada, Pakistan, Iran, Australia, Italy, Spain and Norway are the other participating teams.                                                                                                                     
